President Obama has announced his intent to nominate Lee E. Goodman as Commissioner of the Federal Election Commission. Goodman is currently a Partner at the law firm LeClairRyan and has previous experience as Counsel at Wiley Rein LLP. He has also worked in various positions for the Governor of Virginia and served as Counsel to the Attorney General of Virginia. Goodman holds a B.A. and J.D. from the University of Virginia.